The probability that any single observation is less than $\pi_{0.7}$ is 0.7 because $\pi_{0.7}$ is the 70th percentile. Thus, the probability that an observation is greater than or equal to $\pi_{0.7}$ is $1 - 0.7 = 0.3$.

