## Step 3: Determine the percentage of patients with irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure
Given that 17% have an irregular heartbeat and 35% of those have high blood pressure, we can calculate the percentage of patients with both irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure. This is $17\% \times 35\% = 0.17 \times 0.35 = 0.0595$ or $5.95\%$.

## Step 4: Calculate the percentage of patients with irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure
