The problem involves computing the probability of the intersection of two independent events, A and B, given their individual probabilities. Independent events are those where the occurrence or non-occurrence of one event does not affect the probability of the occurrence of the other event.

## Step 2: Recall the formula for the probability of the intersection of two independent events.
For independent events A and B, the probability of both events occurring (the intersection of A and B) is given by $P(A \cap B) = P(A) \times P(B)$.

